timeline.bodyText:
The replacement below is subtle - it took me a bit to figure out (a) why it was needed,  (b) what was so special about ~1.    This is explained in https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6901 - which mentions the need to replace '~' in addition to the need to replace '/'.
(1) Should this fix also take the opportunity to replace all '~' with '~0'? (I vote yes.)
(2) Please consider adding a comment that's something like:
// We must encode each '/' and '~' in a JSON patch token using '~1' and '~0', otherwise
// the JSON patch will incorrectly treat '/' and '~' as special delimiters. (RFC 6901).
// The resulting patched JSON will have '/' and '~' within the token (not ~0 or ~1).

